    "bio": [
      "👋 Hi! I'm <strong>Atharva Mandavkar</strong>, a passionate Electronics and Communication Engineering student from <span class=\"text-blue-400\">MIT World Peace University, Pune</span>, graduating in March 2025.",
      "🚀 I specialize in <strong class=\"text-green-400\">Machine Learning</strong>, <strong class=\"text-purple-400\">Computer Vision</strong>, and <strong class=\"text-yellow-400\">IoT Systems</strong>. My journey has been driven by a desire to solve real-world problems using AI and embedded technologies.",
      "🏆 I've had the privilege of winning multiple national hackathons including <strong class=\"text-yellow-400\">Smart India Hackathon 2023</strong> and <strong class=\"text-blue-400\">eYantra Innovation Challenge 2023-24</strong>, where our team won the Best Implementation Award at the National Finals.",
      "🤖 Recently achieved a significant milestone with a <strong class=\"text-purple-400\">published patent</strong> on <strong class=\"text-cyan-400\">\"AI-Driven Crime Detection using Existing CCTV Networks\"</strong> (Publication No: 03/2026). The system leverages advanced machine learning and video transformers to enhance surveillance with real-time anomaly detection and intelligent alerting.",
      "💡 My expertise lies in developing end-to-end AI-ML solutions—from training deep learning models using <span class=\"text-pink-400\">PyTorch</span> and <span class=\"text-orange-400\">YOLOv8</span> to deploying them on edge devices like Raspberry Pi and STM32 microcontrollers.",
      "🎯 When I'm not coding, I'm exploring new technologies, participating in workshops, or contributing to innovative projects that make a difference. I believe in continuous learning and pushing the boundaries of what's possible with technology."
    ],
